                            <comment id="13695245" author="smarthi" created="Fri, 28 Jun 2013 04:55:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is only seen when running with Complimentary Naive Bayes or Naive Bayes options.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;seqdirectory now executes as a MapReduce job (in light of the changes in Mahout-833) unless the sequential option is explicitly specified.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;classify-20newsgroups.sh creates 20new-seq/ directory on the first run, but subsequent runs fail as the directory already exists from the previous runs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix was to specify --overwrite flag when invoking seqdirectory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
